<p><date when="1824-11-06">November 6th 1824</date></p>
<p>Dear Sir</p>

<p>I promised to Select a Track of Land for <persName>Doct. Keep</persName> and one
for <persName>Thomas Purvis</persName> and <persName>Capt. Brown</persName> and for the <persName>Randols</persName>. But in
consequence of my Bad health and other Misfortunes I shall not be
able to attend to it and must request you to make the selections for
them, as to my Own Business I Leave it to yourself and <persName>J. P.
Coles</persName> to decide on it as you may Think proper which will be 
satisfactory to me I have Explaind my self to <persName>Coles</persName>&#8212;whom will 
Explain to you   I am in Bad helth But something on the mend</p>

<p><persName>J E Groce</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Col. S F Austin Political chief and Jud of the 
<placeName>Colony</placeName></persName>   <persName>J. P. Coles</persName></p>



        </div1>
    </body>
